other_tests.findings: Increase in bibasilar atelectasis, more on the left than the right. No pleural or pericardial effusion is noted. A mildly enhancing lesion in segment VII noted, unchanged in size. Thickening of the gastric and transverse portion of the duodenum seen previously is not visualized. No cholelithiasis or signs of cholecystitis. No renal stones. No intraabdominal air or fluid. Three areas of focal inflammatory processes noted: a 1.8-cm cyst with air blockage adjacent to sigmoid loop, a 1.6 x 1.9 cm abscess in the left hemipelvis, and a sinus tract with contrast leakage anterior to the uterus.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The previously noted process has progressed with the appearance of new areas of focal inflammatory processes including cysts and abscesses.
